Array Advantages and Disadvantages

Array Advantages and Disadvantages
There are advantages and disadvantages when using arrays.

-Advantages of Arrays-
simplifies programs for processing repetitive code, rotating data, and performing table lookup
fast processing time because the array is stored in memory
potentially eliminates the need for multiple steps
ability to use non-sorted data

-Disadvantages of Arrays-
size of array defined at compile time
cannot combine character and numeric elements in an array
must use a numeric value to reference an element
returns only a single value when referencing an element

  
